 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W2-007: Fix Phi divergence metric to use link-based traceability instead of entity-set overlap. PROBLEM: trilateral.rs:200-211 compute_phi() computes D_IS by counting intent entities NOT in the spec entity set (by entity ID). The spec (spec/18-trilateral.md:74-78) defines D_IS as entities lacking :spec/traces-to LINKS. An intent entity sharing an EntityId with a spec entity would be falsely counted as 'linked'. An intent entity with a String-valued :spec/traces-to link to SEED.md would be falsely counted as 'unlinked' because the check is entity-set membership, not link existence. SOLUTION: Rewrite compute_phi() to count :spec/traces-to and :impl/implements link datoms. D_IS = count of intent entities with no outgoing :spec/traces-to Ref datom. D_SP = count of spec entities with no incoming :impl/implements Ref datom. Use VAET index for reverse reference traversal. VERIFICATION: (1) Unit test: intent entity with :spec/traces-to Ref → D_IS counts as linked. (2) Unit test: intent entity with String :spec/traces-to → D_IS counts as unlinked (String, not Ref). (3) proptest: D_IS + D_SP <= total entities in ISP projections. DEPENDS-ON: W1-002 (trilateral namespace partitions from policy). INTERACTS-WITH: W0-005 (retraction affects link existence), W1-004 (views must track links correctly)."
